11 DEVELOPER CHOICE FOR PERFORMANCE GUARANTEES FOR DRIVEWAY
12 AND ENCROACHMENT PROJECTS
13 SECTION 11.(a) G.S. 136-93 reads as rewritten:
14 "§ 136-93. Openings, structures, pipes, trees, and issuance of permits.
15 (a) No opening or other interference whatsoever shall be made in any State road or
16 highway other than streets not maintained by the Department of Transportation in cities and
17 towns, nor shall any structure be placed thereon, nor shall any structure which has been placed
18 thereon be changed or removed except in accordance with a written permit from the Department
19 of Transportation or its duly authorized officers, who shall exercise complete and permanent
20 control over such roads and highways. No State road or State highway, other than streets not
21 maintained by the Department of Transportation in cities and towns, shall be dug up for laying
22 or placing pipes, conduits, sewers, wires, railways, or other objects, and no obstruction placed
23 thereon, without a written permit as hereinbefore provided for, and then only in accordance with
24 the regulations of said Department of Transportation or its duly authorized officers or employees;
25 and the work shall be under the supervision and to the satisfaction of the Department of
26 Transportation or its officers or employees, and the entire expense of replacing the highway in
27 as good condition as before shall be paid by the persons, firms, or corporations to whom the
28 permit is given, or by whom the work is done. The Department of Transportation, or its duly
29 authorized officers, may, in its discretion, before granting a permit under the provisions of this
30 section, require the applicant to file a satisfactory bond, payable to performance guarantee in
31 favor of the State of North Carolina, in such an amount as may be deemed sufficient by the
32 Department of Transportation or its duly authorized officers, conditioned upon the proper
33 compliance with the requirements of this section by the person, firm, or corporation granted such
34 permit. The form of the performance guarantee may consist of a bond, irrevocable letter of credit,
35 parent guaranty, or other instrument that provides equivalent security to a surety bond or
36 irrevocable letter of credit at the election of the applicant. Any person making any opening in a
37 State road or State highway, or placing any structure thereon, or changing or removing any
38 structure thereon without obtaining a written permit as herein provided, or not in compliance
39 with the terms of such permit, or otherwise violating the provisions of this section, shall be guilty
40 of a Class 1 misdemeanor: Provided, this section shall not apply to railroad crossings. The
41 railroads shall keep up said crossings as now provided by law.
42 …."
43 SECTION 11.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to permit
44 applications filed on or after that date.
